      <unittitle encodinganalog="245">Leon Ramsey papers <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="245$f" normal="1917/1919">1917-1919</unitdate>, <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="245$f" normal="1960/1969" certainty="approximate">1960s</unitdate></unittitle>
      <abstract>Soldier from Armada, Mich., member of Headquarters Company, 339th U.S. Infantry who served in the Allied intervention in Russia, 1918-1920, the "Polar Bear Expedition." Collection includes correspondence describing his experiences in the army during training at Camp Custer, Mich., and during his service in Russia; also miscellanea, photographs, and a paper based on Ramsey's correspondence, probably written by John O. Ramsey.</abstract>
      <unitid countrycode="us" repositorycode="MiU-H" encodinganalog="099" type="call number">9526 Aa 2</unitid>
      <langmaterial>The materials are in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English.</language></langmaterial>
      <repository>
        <corpname encodinganalog="852"><subarea>Bentley Historical Library</subarea> University of Michigan</corpname>
        <extptr href="bhladd" show="embed" actuate="onload"/>
      </repository>
    </did>
    <descgrp type="admin">
      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
        <p>The collection was donated by John Ramsey, of La Canada, California, in 1995 (Donor no.: <num type="donor" encodinganalog="541$e">8362</num>).</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict encodinganalog="506">
        <p>The collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite encodinganalog="524">
        <p>item, folder title, box no., Leon Ramsey papers, Bentley Historical Library, University of Michigan</p>
      </prefercite>
    </descgrp>
    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Resident of <geogname normal="Armada (Mich.)">Armada, Mich.</geogname>, served with <corpname normal="United States. Army. Infantry, 339th. Headquarters Company.">Headquarters Co.</corpname>, 339th Infantry.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p><genreform normal="Correspondence.">Correspondence</genreform> describing his experiences in the army during training at <geogname normal="Fort Custer (Mich.)">Camp Custer, Mich.</geogname>, and during his service in Russia; also miscellanea, and a paper based on <persname normal="Ramsey, Leon, 1897-">Ramsey's</persname> <genreform normal="Correspondence.">correspondence</genreform>, probably written by <persname normal="Ramsey, John O.">John O. Ramsey</persname>. <genreform normal="Photographs.">Photographs</genreform> include a <genreform normal="Portraits.">portrait</genreform> (in uniform) and <genreform normal="Postcards.">postcards</genreform> of <geogname normal="Fort Custer (Mich.)">Camp Custer, Mich.</geogname>, and <geogname normal="Arkhangel'sk (Russia)">Archangel.</geogname></p>
    </scopecontent>
